description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a Band 7 acute inpatient stroke physiotherapist 12 month maternity leave cover post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following the move of the acute stroke service to QMC you will be based on this campus, with the rehabilitation beds being located on the City campus of NUH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team is audited by the SSNAP data base and regularly scores an A.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an expectation that you will be highly engaged with the stroke service and actively involved in service developments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a great team, led by highly motivated and experienced Band 7&#39;s and an 8a clinical lead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team of dynamic high performers feature both rotational band 6 &amp; band 5 staff as well as support workers at band 3 &amp; band 2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have a passion for developing and supporting staff and a track record of undertaking high quality practical training and supervision of students and allocated clinical staff of all grades.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service operates at a weekend as well as Monday to Friday so you will be expected to actively participate in this weekend service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDave WhittakerJob titleTherapy Service ManagerEmail addressdavid.whittaker@nuh.nhs.ukTelephone number07812268385&lt;/p&gt;
